      <h1 class="title"> Title II & VII Policy </h1>
      <h5> Last Updated: <time>August 22nd, 2025</time>. </h5>
      <h5> Into Effect: <time>September 3rd, 2025</time>. </h5>
      <p class="my-3">
        <i>Our only current active volunteering service is the <a href="https://beta-testing.atproducts.xyz">Department of Beta Testing</a>. No current employment opportunities is being offered.</i>
      </p>
      <p class="my-3">
        <i>All of these titles refer to the <a href="https://www.archives.gov/milestone-documents/civil-rights-act">Civil Rights Act of 1964</a>. </i>
      </p>
      <h3>Title II Policy</h3>
      <p> It is the policy of AT Products LLC that all customers, partners, and other individuals shall not be discriminated against due to sex, race, color, national origin, religion, or disability. No customer or any other person will be subject to discrimination in any of our services.</p>
      <h3>Title VII Policy</h3>
      <p> It is the policy of AT Products LLC that all employment and volunteering opportunities will be offered without regard to sex, race, color, national origin, religion, or disability and that no employee, volunteer, or any other person will be subject to discrimination. We will accommodate religious practices dependent on employees and volunteers.</p>
      <h3>Contact Points</h3>
      <p>
        If you have inquiries, require clarifications, or wish to report concerns regarding potential violations of the Title II and Title VII policies, please use one of the following contact methods:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Contact Form:</strong> <a href="/contact">/contact</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:support@atproducts.xyz">support@atproducts.xyz</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Better Business Bureau (BBB):</strong> Formal complaints can also be submitted through the <a href="https://www.bbb.org">BBB website</a>.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        AT Products LLC is committed to addressing all correspondence in a timely and professional manner, in compliance with applicable civil rights regulations and internal policies. Reports of suspected violations will be thoroughly reviewed and investigated.
      </p>
      </main>
